[Black "Chapter 6 Paulsen Formation"]

{In Chapters 6 and 7, Black builds on the Kan foundation of ...e6 and a6 before the paths diverge. With ...Nc6, the defender opts for the Paulsen and plans to refute the gambit via ...Nge7, Ng6, Be7 and O-O. The gambiteer halts Black's development with Bg5, provoking ...f6/h6.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 e6 6. Bc4 {[%entry]} a6 (6... Nge7 7. Bg5 f6 (7... h6 8. Nb5 d5 9. exd5 hxg5 (9... exd5? 10. Bf4 Qa5+ 11. b4 Qxb4+ 12. Bd2) 10. dxc6 Nxc6 11. Qxd8+ Kxd8 12. O-O-O+ Ke7 13. Nxg5 g6 14. Kb1) 8. Be3 Ng6 9. O-O Be7 10. Nb5 O-O 11. Rc1 a6 12. Nd6 Qc7 13. Nf5) 7. O-O Nge7 (7... Qc7 8. Nd5!? exd5 9. exd5 Nce7 (9... Na5 10. Bd3 d6?! 11. Bd2 Be7 12. Rc1 Qd8 13. Qe1! b6 14. b4 Nb7 15. Nd4) 10. Bb3 d6 11. Re1 Nf6 (11... g6 12. Qd4 f6) 12. Bf4 Bg4 13. Rc1 Qd7 14. Qd4) 8. Bg5 f6 (8... h6 9. Be3 b5 10. Bb3 Bb7 11. Re1 Na5 12. Ne5 Nxb3 (12... d6 13. Nxf7) 13. Bb6 Qc8) 9. Be3 Ng6 (9... b5 10. Bb3 Na5 11. Nd4) 10. Bb3 b5 (10... Be7 11. Na4 O-O 12. Nb6 Rb8) 11. Nd5 exd5 12. exd5 Nce5 13. d6 Bb7 14. Nxe5 fxe5 15. f4 exf4 16. Re1 fxe3 17. Rxe3+ Be7 18. Qd4 Qc8 19. Rae1 Qc6 20. R1e2 Qc1+ 21. Re1 Qc6 22. Rf3 *

